   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The Symmetry screen shows the trend graphs for the symmetry.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The symmetry of a region is the difference in the amount of infrared radiation (= glass) between the left (L) and the right (R) part.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Symmetry = abs ((L-R) / (L+R)) * 100%. For example:<ul id="ul_zt2_jsn_fcc" class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Left radiation = L = 60; </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Right radiation = R = 40;</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Symmetry = abs ((60-40)/(60+40))*100% = 20% </li>
         </ul>
